{"parentUuid":"d1e03119-ee7d-453e-af0f-aa5d42e28ec6","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspaces/agent-feed/prod","sessionId":"892909d3-aa5f-4e15-a679-572d401e85fb","version":"1.0.120","gitBranch":"v1","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-20250514","id":"msg_01UrJp6v3EgRaGePT9oFUbBE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Experimental Demonstrations\n\n### Bell Test Experiments\nThe most famous experiments testing entanglement are Bell tests, which demonstrate violations of Bell's inequality:\n\n1. **Alain Aspect's Experiments (1981-1982)**: Used polarized photons to show correlations stronger than classical physics allows\n2. **Modern Loophole-Free Tests**: Recent experiments have closed all known loopholes, definitively proving quantum entanglement\n\n### Key Experimental Results\n- **Correlation Strength**: Entangled particles show correlations up to √2 times stronger than classical mechanics predicts\n- **Instantaneous Correlations**: Measurements appear instantaneous regardless of distance (tested up to hundreds of kilometers)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":418,"cache_read_input_tokens":42173,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":418,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CUabE8EU6H4Wv6m8aZTLQ","type":"assistant","uuid":"c2a3bbc2-4182-4c6a-b604-23500dab299b","timestamp":"2025-10-29T01:04:52.671Z"}
